H.B. 568
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Mar 27, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40315-LR-150A
Short Title: 2025 Omnibus Labor Amendments.-AB (Public)
Sponsors: Representative K. Hall.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT MAKING OMNIBUS AMENDMENTS TO LAWS PERTAINING TO THE NORTH
3 CAROLINA DEPARTMENT OF LABOR.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.1. Article 16 of Chapter 95 of the General Statutes is amended by
6 adding a new section to read:
7 "§ 95-136.2. Commissioner and employees not subject to subpoena for testimony except in
8 certain circumstances.
9 (a) Neither the Commissioner nor any employee or former employee of the Department
10 is subject to a subpoena for appearance for purposes of inquiry into any occupational safety and
11 health inspection, except in one of the following circumstances:
12 (1) An enforcement proceeding is brought under this Article.
13 (2) An action is filed in which the Department is a party.
14 (3) The Commissioner consents in writing to waive the exemption provided by
15 this section.
16 (4) A court finds all of the following:
17 a. The information sought is essential to the underlying case.
18 b. There are no reasonable alternative means for acquiring the
19 information.
20 c. A significant injustice would occur if the requested testimony was not
21 available.
22 (b) The party that issued the subpoena shall pay to the Department a witness fee in the
23 amount of five hundred dollars ($500.00) per day.
24 (c) This section does not apply to a subpoena requesting only documents or other
25 records."
26 SECTION 1.2. G.S. 150B-21.5 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
27 "(c1) OSHA Standard. – The Occupational Safety and Health Division of the Department
28 of Labor is not required to publish a notice of text in the North Carolina Register or hold a public
29 hearing when it proposes to adopt a rule that concerns an occupational safety and health standard
30 that is identical to a federal regulation promulgated by the Secretary of the United States
31 Department of Labor. The Division shall file the rule with the Commission for the purpose of
32 receiving written objections to the rule in accordance with G.S. 150B-21.3(b2)."
33 SECTION 1.3.(a) G.S. 95-135(d) reads as rewritten:
34 "(d) Every official act of the Commission shall be entered of record and its hearings and
35 records shall be open to the public. The Commission is authorized and empowered to make such
36 procedural rules as are necessary for the orderly transaction of its proceedings. Unless the
*DRH40315-LR-150A*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 Commission adopts a different rule, the proceedings, as nearly as possible, shall be in accordance
2 with the Rules of Civil Procedure, G.S. 1A-1. The Commission may order testimony to be taken
3 by deposition in any proceeding pending before it at any stage of such proceeding. Any person,
4 firm or corporation, and its agents or officials, may be compelled to appear and testify and
5 produce like documentary evidence before the Commission. Commission, except that upon
6 motion of a respondent, the Commission shall require prehearing discovery, order that testimony
7 be taken by deposition, compel production of documents, and compel persons to appear.
8 Witnesses whose depositions are taken under this section, and the persons taking such
9 depositions, shall be entitled to the same fees as are paid for like services in the courts of the
10 State."
11 SECTION 1.3.(b) This section shall apply to citations issued on or after the effective
12 date of this act.
13 SECTION 1.4. G.S. 130A-385(e) reads as rewritten:
14 "(e) In cases where death occurred due to an injury received in the course of the decedent's
15 employment, the Chief Medical Examiner shall forward to the Commissioner of Labor a copy of
16 the medical examiner's report of the investigation, including the location of the fatal injury and
17 the name and address of the decedent's employer at the time of the fatal injury. The Chief Medical
18 Examiner shall forward this report within 30 days of receipt of the information from the medical
19 examiner. Upon written request by the Commissioner of Labor, the Chief Medical Examiner
20 shall provide the finalized autopsy report within five months of the date of the request."
21 SECTION 1.5. G.S. 95-36.3(c) reads as rewritten:
22 "(c) The Commissioner of Labor, with the written approval of the Attorney General as to
23 legality, shall have power to adopt, alter, amend or repeal appropriate rules of procedure for
24 selection of the arbitrator or panel and for conduct of the arbitration proceedings in accordance
25 with this Article: Provided, however, that such rules shall be inapplicable to the extent that they
26 are inconsistent with the arbitration agreement of the parties."
27 SECTION 1.6.(a) G.S. 95-110.2 reads as rewritten:
28 "§ 95-110.2. Scope.
29 This Article shall govern the design, construction, installation, plans review, testing,
30 inspection, certification, operation, use, maintenance, alteration, relocation and investigation of
31 accidents involving:
32 (1) Elevators, dumbwaiters, escalators, and moving walks;
33 (2) Personnel hoists;
34 (3) Inclined stairway chair lifts;
35 (4) Inclined and vertical wheelchair lifts;
36 (5) Manlifts; and
37 (6) Special equipment.
38 This Article shall not apply to devices and equipment located and operated in a single family
39 residence, residence. This Article shall not apply to conveyors and related equipment within the
40 scope of the American National Standard Safety Standard for Conveyors and Related Equipment
41 (ANSI/ASME B20.1) constructed, installed and used exclusively for the movement of materials,
42 or to mining equipment specifically covered by the Federal Mine Safety and Health Act or the
43 Mine Safety and Health Act of North Carolina or the rules and regulations adopted pursuant
44 thereto."
45 SECTION 1.6.(b) G.S. 95-110.3 reads as rewritten:
46 "§ 95-110.3. Definitions.
47 (a) The term "Commissioner" shall mean the North Carolina Commissioner of Labor or
48 his the Commissioner's authorized representative.
49 (b) The term "Director" shall mean the Director of the Elevator and Amusement Device
50 Division Bureau of the North Carolina Department of Labor.
51 …."
