1 SECTION 1.6.(c) G.S. 95-110.4 reads as rewritten:
2 "§ 95-110.4. Elevator and Amusement Device Division Bureau established.
3 There is hereby created an Elevator and Amusement Device Division Bureau within the
4 Department of Labor. The Commissioner shall appoint a director of the Elevator and Amusement
5 Device Division Bureau and such other employees as the Commissioner deems necessary to
6 assist the director in administering the provisions of this Article."
7 SECTION 1.6.(d) G.S. 95-110.5 reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 95-110.5. Powers and duties of Commissioner.
9 The Commissioner of Labor is hereby empowered:empowered to do all of the following:
10 (1) To delegate to the Director of the Elevator and Amusement Device Division
11 Bureau such powers, duties and responsibilities as the Commissioner
12 determines will best serve the public interest in the safe operation of lifting
13 devices and equipment;equipment.
14 (2) To supervise the Director of the Elevator and Amusement Device
15 Division;Bureau.
16 (3) To adopt, modify, or revoke such rules and regulations as are necessary for
17 the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Article including, but not
18 limited to, those governing the design, construction, installation, plans review,
19 testing, inspection, certification, operation, use, maintenance, alteration and
20 relocation of devices and equipment subject to the provisions of this Article.
21 The rules and regulations promulgated pursuant to this rulemaking authority
22 shall conform with good engineering practice as evidenced generally by the
23 most recent editions of the American National Standard Safety Code for
24 Elevators, Dumbwaiters, Escalators and Moving Walks, the National
25 Electrical Code, the American National Standard Safety Requirements for
26 Personnel Hoists, the American National Standard Safety Code for Manlifts,
27 the American National Standard Safety Standard for Conveyors and Related
28 Equipment and similar codes promulgated by agencies engaged in research
29 concerning strength of material, safe design, and other factors bearing upon
30 the safe operation of the devices and equipment subject to the provisions of
31 this Article. The rules and regulations may apply different standards to devices
32 and equipment subject to this Article depending upon their date of installation.
33 The rules and regulations for special equipment shall not adopt specifically
34 any portion of the American National Standard Safety Code for Elevators,
35 Dumbwaiters, Escalators and Moving Walks to inclined and vertical
36 reciprocating conveyors;conveyors.
37 (4) To enforce rules and regulations adopted under authority of this
38 Article;Article.
39 (5) To inspect and have tested for acceptance all new, altered or relocated devices
40 or equipment subject to the provisions of this Article;Article.
41 (6) To make maintenance and periodic inspections and tests of all devices and
42 equipment subject to the provisions of this Article as often as every six
43 months;months.
44 (7) To issue certificates of operation which certify for use such devices and
45 equipment as are found to be in compliance with this Article and the rules and
46 regulations promulgated thereunder;thereunder.
47 (8) To have free access, with or without notice, to the devices and equipment
48 subject to the provisions of this Article, during reasonable hours, for purposes
49 of inspection or testing;testing.
