1 (9) To obtain an Administrative Search and Inspection Warrant in accordance
2 with the provisions of Article 4A of Chapter 15 of the General
3 Statutes;Statutes.
4 (10) To investigate accidents involving the devices and equipment subject to the
5 provisions of this Article to determine the cause of such accident, and he shall
6 have full subpoena powers in conducting such investigation;investigation.
7 (11) To institute proceedings in the civil or criminal courts of this State, when a
8 provision of this Article or the rules and regulations promulgated thereunder
9 has been violated;violated.
10 (12) To issue a limited certificate of operation for any device or equipment subject
11 to the provisions of this Article to allow the temporary or restricted use
12 thereof;thereof.
13 (13) To adopt, modify or revoke rules and regulations governing the qualifications
14 of inspectors;inspectors. The Commissioner may waive or amend the
15 American National Safety Standards from the American National Standards
16 Institute as those standards relate to the qualifications of inspectors in this
17 State if the Commissioner sets alternative standards that are reasonably
18 equivalent, as determined by the Commissioner.
19 (14) To grant exceptions from the requirements of the rules and regulations
20 promulgated under authority of this Article and to permit the use of other
21 devices when such exceptions and uses will not expose the public to an unsafe
22 condition likely to result in serious personal injury or property
23 damage;damage.
24 (15) To require that a construction permit must be obtained from the Commissioner
25 before any device or equipment subject to the provisions of this Article is
26 installed, altered or moved from one place to another and to require that the
27 Commissioner must be supplied with whatever plans, diagrams or other data
28 he deems necessary to determine whether or not the proposed construction is
29 in compliance with the provisions of this Article and the rules and regulations
30 promulgated thereunder;thereunder.
31 (16) To prohibit the use of any device or equipment subject to the provisions of
32 this Article which is found upon inspection to expose the public to an unsafe
33 condition likely to cause personal injury or property damage. Such device or
34 equipment shall be made operational only upon the Commissioner's
35 determination that such device or equipment has been made safe;safe.
36 (17) To order the payment of all civil penalties provided by this Article. Funds
37 collected pursuant to a civil penalty order shall be deposited with the State
38 Treasurer;Treasurer.
39 (18) To require that any device or equipment subject to the provisions of this
40 Article which has been out-of-service and not continuously maintained for one
41 or more years shall not be returned to service without first complying with all
42 rules and regulations governing existing installations; andinstallations.
43 (19) To coordinate enforcement and inspection activity relative to equipment,
44 devices and operations covered by this Article in order to minimize
45 duplication of liability or regulatory responsibility on the part of the employer
46 or owner.
47 (20) To establish fees not to exceed two hundred dollars ($200.00) one thousand
48 dollars ($1,000) for the inspection and issuance of certificates of operation for
49 all devices and equipment subject to this Article upon installation or alteration,
50 for each follow-up inspection, and for annual periodic inspections thereafter."
